cs.MS, cs.CG, cs.CE, cs.NA, cs.ME 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is the most likely category as the paper presents a computational method for the design of architected truss lattice materials using numerical homogenization and density-based topology optimization. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the paper uses the geometry projection method to map parameters onto a continuous density field for the primal and sensitivity analysis. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is another possible category as the paper applies the method to design lattice structures with extremized effective properties. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper uses numerical homogenization to obtain effective properties. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper focuses on the design of architected truss lattice materials.
